Should Schools Provide Free Pads and Tampons?

Have you ever experienced period shaming, or â€œperiod poverty"? Should schools step in to help? Should schools be required to provide free pads and tampons to students? How are pads and tampons similar to toilet paper, soap, Band-Aids and other products that are already provided in schools? How are they different?

---

In my opinion,

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: , girls should be able to buy whatever products they might need for their menstruation without any worry.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Thus , providing pads and tampons can help limit the period shaming, and period poverty that female students are regularly subject to.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: for a period of time, as long as one continues to wear them, and have to be changed out every while.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I am sure that students would appreciate seeing them in the school, just as they would any other supply readily available in school.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: For example, there should not be any announcement in an auditorium or over the intercom that the student need pads.
